text: Aleksa Gold (born 3 January 2000) is an Estonian swimmer. She competed in the women's 200 metre freestyle at the 2019 World Aquatics Championships and she did not advance to compete in the semi-finals. ==References== Category:2000 births Category:Living people Category:Estonian female swimmers Category:Estonian female freestyle swimmers Category:Place of birth missing (living people) Category:Swimmers at the 2018 Summer Youth Olympics
